properties.headline: Special Weather Statement issued February 9 at 6:23AM CST by NWS Green Bay WI
properties.description:
Snow will overspread the area this morning. At 600 am, the leading
edge of the snow extended from Eau Claire, to the Wisconsin
Dells, to near Milwaukee. The snow was advancing rapidly east, and
should begin in central Wisconsin by 800 am, and in northern and
eastern Wisconsin by late morning.

Once the snow begins, it will rapidly become heavy in central and
east-central Wisconsin. Snowfall rates of 1 inch per hour are
likely in these areas, with rates approaching 2 inches per hour
possible. The heaviest snow will move through through central
Wisconsin between about 900 am and noon, and and through east-
central Wisconsin during the late morning and early afternoon
hours. A few flashes of lightning and claps of thunder could
accompany the heavy snow.

The snow will continue into the afternoon, though snowfall rates
will be lower than with the initial burst of heavy snow. Snow
will begin to diminish to flurries across central Wisconsin toward
dusk and in eastern Wisconsin during the early to middle evening.
The total snowfall from the storm is expected to range from
around an inch in far northern Vilas county, to 6 to 10 inches
across central and east-central Wisconsin.

Travel conditions are likely to deteriorate quickly this morning
due to the snow. Although winds are not expected to be strong with
this storm, the visibility in central and east-central Wisconsin
will also be significantly reduced at times due to the falling
snow. Be sure to allow plenty of time to reach your destination
if you are traveling today.

NWSheadline: RAPID ONSET OF HEAVY SNOW LIKELY TO PRODUCE QUICKLY DETERIORATING TRAVEL CONDITIONS ACROSS MOST OF THE AREA THIS MORNING
